# FIX_FORWARD 7.3: prevent stale-dist commits. Every package consumed via
# its `dist/` (notably @friday/shared) must be rebuilt before any commit so
# the artifacts in the staged source tree match the source itself.
#
# Scoped to `packages/**` — those are the workspaces other packages import
# from at runtime. Building `services/dashboard` here was actively harmful:
# vite emits hashed chunk filenames (`build/server/chunks/1-<hash>.js`),
# and a running `node build/index.js` keeps its old manifest in memory
# pointing at the previous hashes. A commit then silently breaks the live
# dashboard's next route load with `ERR_MODULE_NOT_FOUND`. Services'
# `dist/` and `build/` are gitignored anyway; they're only consumed by
# `friday start <service>`, which builds what it needs at boot time.
#
# turbo's build cache makes this cheap on no-source-change commits and
# correct on source-change commits. If you're committing a one-line README
# fix and want to skip the build, pass `--no-verify` — but the default is
# to never trust dist drift past a commit boundary.
pnpm exec turbo build --filter=./packages/**
